<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-37-0096 </DOCNO><TEXT>This conference examines the development of cogeneration and parallelgeneration in Canada. Background papers review the experience of cogenerationin the U.S., and provide an overview of parallel generation activitiesin Canada. The potential for parallel generation is presented for industryand use of renewable energy sources. Technologies for cogeneration arereviewed. The economics, financing, and contractural arrangements forcogeneration projects are examined. The perspectives of electric andnatural gas utilities are presented. Public policy issues are discussed.Twenty abstracts were prepared from this conference.</TEXT></DOC>